org.libav.avresample

Interface IAudioResampleContextWrapper

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IWrapper
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AudioResampleContextWrapperLAVC, AudioResampleContextWrapperLAVR

    public interface IAudioResampleContextWrapper
extends IWrapper
    Wrapper for the AVAudioResampleContextWrapper. It provides access to some of the AVAudioResampleContextWrapper properties and also it allows to work with the resample context using the Libav functions.
    Author:
    Ondrej Perutka

      • getMatrix

        double[] getMatrix(int stride)
                   throws LibavException
        Get current mixing matrix.

        NOTE: The method may not be supported if the avresample library is not present.
        Parameters:
        stride - distance between adjacent input channels in the matrix array
        Returns:
        mixing coefficients; matrix[i + stride * o] is the weight of input channel i in output channel o
        Throws:
        LibavException

      • setMatrix

        void setMatrix(double[] matrix,
             int stride)
               throws LibavException
        Set custom mixing matrix. It overrides the default mixing matrix.

        NOTE: The method may not be supported if the avresample library is not present.
        Parameters:
        matrix - mixing coefficients; matrix[i + stride * o] is the weight of input channel i in output channel o
        stride - distance between adjacent input channels in the matrix array
        Throws:
        LibavException

      • convert

        int convert(Pointer<Pointer<?>> output,
          int outPlaneSize,
          int outSampleCount,
          Pointer<Pointer<?>> input,
          int inPlaneSize,
          int inSampleCount)
            throws LibavException
        Convert input samples and write them to the output FIFO. The output data can be null or have fewer allocated samples than required. In this case, any remaining samples not written to the output will be added to an internal FIFO buffer, to be returned at the next call to this method. At the end of the conversion process, there may be data remaining in the internal FIFO buffer. Call this method with null input to get this data as output.
        Parameters:
        output - output data pointers
        outPlaneSize - output plane size
        outSampleCount - maximum number of samples that the output buffer can hold
        input - input data pointers
        inPlaneSize - input plane size
        inSampleCount - number of input samples to convert
        Returns:
        number of samples written to the output buffer, not including converted samples added to the internal output FIFO
        Throws:
        LibavException
